---
import Footer from '@components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '@components/Header.astro';
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Configuring Flutter Linux Mint">
  <body>
    <div class="my-container">
      <Header />
      <main>
        <div class="flex-grid">
          <div class="container post">
            <div class="inner">
              <div class="page-title">
                <h1>How to Configure Flutter and Android Studio on Linux Mint</h1>
                <p>4/15/2022</p>
              </div>
              <div class="centered-div">
                <ol>
                  <li>Download <a href="https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install/linux">Flutter</a> (I used snap)</li>
                  <li>Run <code>flutter doctor</code></li>
                  <li>Download <a href="https://developer.android.com/studio">Android Studio</a>. Save to <code>~/Download</code></li>
                  <li><code>cd ~/Download</code> then <code>tar -xzf &ltandroid_studio_tgz&gt</code></li>
                  <li><code>sudo mv &ltandroid_studio_dir&gt /usr/local</code></li>
                  <li>Create symlink in <code>/usr/local/bin</code> : <code>ln -s /usr/local/<android_studio_dir>/bin/studio.sh studio.sh</code>. You will now be able to start from command line or i3bar with <code>studio.sh</code></li>
                  <li>Install <a href="https://www.google.com/chrome/">Chrome</a></li>
                  <li>Configure Android SDK path for Flutter: <code>flutter config --android-sdk /home/&ltuser_name&gt/Android/Sdk</code></li>
                  <li>Use Android studio to get the remaining command line tools: <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/60529140">StackOverflow instructions</a></li>
                  <li>Set licenses: <code>flutter doctor --android-licenses</code></li>
                  <li>Run <code>flutter doctor</code></li>
                </ol>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </main>
      <Footer />
    </div>
  </body>
</Layout>